## 3. Tiny wrapper – `pcapng.ml`

```ocaml
(* ------------- pcapng.ml -------------
   This file only exposes the abstract type and forwards the three primitives.
   It is optional – you could also `external`‑declare the primitives directly
   in the .mli file – but keeping a short .ml makes the library easier to
   extend later.
*)

type t = private Obj.t   (* abstract – only the C stub can create values *)

type frame = {
  timestamp    : float;
  captured_len : int;
  original_len : int;
  data         : bytes;
}

external open_file : string -> t = "caml_pcapng_open_file"
external close    : t -> unit = "caml_pcapng_close"
external iter_frames : t -> (frame -> unit) -> unit = "caml_pcapng_iter_frames"
```

