## 4. Build instructions (Dune)

Create a `dune` file in the same directory:

```dune
(library
 (name pcapng)
 (public_name pcapng)
 (foreign_stubs
  (language cxx)               ; we need a C++ compiler
  (names pcapng_stubs))
 (cxx_flags (:standard -std=c++17))
 (libraries
  ;; No OCaml libraries needed other than the runtime, but you may need to
  ;; link against libpcapng if it is a separate shared library.
  )
 (cxx_link_flags (:standard -lpcapng)))   ; adjust if libpcapng is a .a/.so
```

If `libpcapng` is header‑only you can drop the `-lpcapng` flag.  
If it provides a static or shared library, make sure the flag points to the
correct library name and that the library is on the linker search path
(`-L/path/to/lib`).

Now run:

```sh
dune build pcapng
```

The library will be built as `pcapng.cma` / `pcapng.cmxa` (bytecode & native).

